
[1]careen

   CAREEN, v.t. In sea language, to heave or bring a ship to lie on one
   side, for the purpose of calking, repairing, cleansing, or paying over
   with pitch, the other side.

   CAREEN, v.i. To incline to one side, as a ship under a press of sail.
